===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[οργασμός]]''' (''orgasmos'') "orgasm", from '''[[οργάω]]''' (''orgao'') "to swell with moisture".  The word entered English around 1763.

===Noun===
'''orgasm'''
# The [[climax]] or [[peak]] of [[sexual]] pleasure which occurs during sexual activity.

===Verb===
'''orgasm'''
# To have an orgasm.

